text: Jessamine County is a county in the U.S. state of Kentucky. As of the 2020 census, the population was 52,991. Its county seat is Nicholasville. The county was formed in 1798. == Communities == === Cities === * Nicholasville (county seat) * Wilmore == References == Category:1798 establishments in Kentucky Category:Kentucky counties
